# S2-3: Content Moderation Flow - Walkthrough

I have implemented the content moderation flow, allowing users to report inappropriate content and admins to review and act on these reports.

## Changes Made

### Database Schema
- **Modified [User](file:///Users/danielkalo/Documents/CS%207180%20-%20Vibe%20Coding%20%28Python%29/Project%202%20-%20Collective%20Unconscious/client/src/pages/UserProfilePage.jsx#6-129)**: Added `role` field (defaulting to `"USER"`).
- **Modified [Turn](file:///Users/danielkalo/Documents/CS%207180%20-%20Vibe%20Coding%20%28Python%29/Project%202%20-%20Collective%20Unconscious/client/src/pages/LogDetailPage.jsx#23-34)**: Added `isHidden` boolean field.
- **New Model [Report](file:///Users/danielkalo/Documents/CS%207180%20-%20Vibe%20Coding%20%28Python%29/Project%202%20-%20Collective%20Unconscious/server/src/controllers/moderation.controller.js#4-36)**: Tracks reports against turns or logs (reporter token, reason, status).
- **New Model `ModerationAction`**: Records actions taken by moderators.

### Backend Implementation
- **Moderation Controller & Routes**:
    - `POST /api/reports`: Anonymous or authenticated users can flag content.
    - `GET /api/moderation/queue`: Admin-only access to pending reports.
    - `POST /api/moderation/action`: Admin-only capability to `HIDE_TURN`, `CLOSE_LOG`, or `DISMISS`.
- **[requireAdmin](file:///Users/danielkalo/Documents/CS%207180%20-%20Vibe%20Coding%20%28Python%29/Project%202%20-%20Collective%20Unconscious/server/src/middleware/auth.js#156-192) Middleware**: A robust guard that checks for either an `ADMIN` role in a JWT or a shared `X-Admin-Secret` header.
- **Turn Redaction**: Updated the logs controller to automatically replace the content of hidden turns with `[content removed]` for non-admin requests.

### Frontend Implementation
- **[ReportButton](file:///Users/danielkalo/Documents/CS%207180%20-%20Vibe%20Coding%20%28Python%29/Project%202%20-%20Collective%20Unconscious/client/src/components/ReportButton.jsx#4-92) Component**: A small, non-obtrusive component added to each turn and the log header.
- **[ModerationPage](file:///Users/danielkalo/Documents/CS%207180%20-%20Vibe%20Coding%20%28Python%29/Project%202%20-%20Collective%20Unconscious/client/src/pages/ModerationPage.jsx#4-118)**: A dedicated admin dashboard accessible at `/moderation`. It uses an `ADMIN_SECRET` for authorization (stored in `localStorage` for convenience).
- **Updated [LogDetailPage](file:///Users/danielkalo/Documents/CS%207180%20-%20Vibe%20Coding%20%28Python%29/Project%202%20-%20Collective%20Unconscious/client/src/pages/LogDetailPage.jsx#35-281)**: Now displays the report buttons and reflects redacted content.

## Verification Results

### Automated Tests
I added a comprehensive test suite [server/__tests__/moderation.test.js](file:///Users/danielkalo/Documents/CS%207180%20-%20Vibe%20Coding%20%28Python%29/Project%202%20-%20Collective%20Unconscious/server/__tests__/moderation.test.js) which covers:
- Reporting turns and logs.
- Admin access and authorization.
- Moderation actions (e.g., hiding a turn).
- Verifying content redaction in the public API.

**All 74 tests in the server suite (including existing ones) are now PASSING.**

```bash
Test Suites: 11 passed, 11 total
Tests:       74 passed, 74 total
```

### Manual Verification Steps
1. **Reporting**: Click the `[report]` link next to any turn, select a reason, and submit.
2. **Moderation**: Visit `/moderation`, enter your `ADMIN_SECRET` (if not set in [.env](file:///Users/danielkalo/Documents/CS%207180%20-%20Vibe%20Coding%20%28Python%29/Project%202%20-%20Collective%20Unconscious/server/.env), the middleware uses it), and review the queue.
3. **Action**: Click "Hide Turn".
4. **Validation**: Go back to the log; the turn content should now show `[content removed]`.
